tals in South America]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1580]]\n[[Category:Port settlements in Argentina]]\n[[Category:Provinces of Argentina]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the capital city of Argentina|the broader conurbation|Greater Buenos Aires|the province|Buenos Aires Province|other uses}}\n{{short description|Capital city and chief port of Argentina}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = City of Buenos Aires\n| official_name                   = Autonomous City of Buenos Aires\n| image_skyline                   = Buenos Aires Photo Montage.png\n| image_caption                   = From top, left to right: view of the [[Buenos Aires Central Business District|Business District]], the [[Palace of the Argentine National Congress|Palace of the Congress]], the [[Puente de la Mujer|Bridge of the Women]], the [[Cabildo of Buenos Aires|Cabildo]], the [[Casa Rosada]], view of [[Puerto Madero]], the [[Caminito]] alley in [[La Boca]], the [[Obelisk of Buenos Aires|Obelisco]] on the intersection of [[9 de Julio Avenue|9 de Julio]] and [[Avenida Corrientes|Corrientes]] avenues and the [[Buenos Aires Metropolitan Cathedral|Metropolitan Cathedral]].\n| image_flag                      = Bandera de la Ciudad de Buenos Aires.svg\n| image_shield                    = Escudo de la Ciudad de Buenos Aires.svg\n| image_blank_emblem              = \n| nickname                        = ''The Queen of [[R\u00edo de la Plata|El Plata]] (La reina del Plata)''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.perfil.com/sociedad/en-la-reina-del-plata-solo-el-3-de-las-calles-tiene-nombre-de-mujer.phtml|title=En la 'Reina del Plata', s\u00f3lo el 3% de las calles tiene nombre de mujer|language=Spanish|last=Corsalini|first=Claudio|date=4 February 2017|accessdate=25 November 2017|work=Perfil|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201103329/http://www.perfil.com/sociedad/en-la-reina-del-plata-so